{"id":"mai-2z13","kind":"comment","edges":[{"type":"on","target":{"kind":"note","ref":"mai-j5hz"}}],"body":"DONE: Full investigation complete. Root cause identified: mergeViaCRDT uses the creation body as the 3-way merge base, which never updates. After N sync cycles, the base diverges increasingly from current content, causing diff operations to produce overlapping insertions that the CRDT faithfully preserves — creating snowball duplication. The CRDT layer (yrs/wasm) works correctly; the bug is in base selection.\n\nFix: Track last-synced content as merge base via a 'ydoc-sync' checkpoint event stored after each successful sync. Use this checkpoint (not creation body) as the base for the next merge.\n\nFindings exported to research ticket mai-t1i8 with complete 9-section analysis including: framing assessment, root cause mechanism, research paths (6 avenues), dead ends (4), key discoveries (4), contradicting evidence analysis, design options (4), testing strategy (13 test cases), and divergent possibilities.","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:08:24Z","branch":"main"}
